LAGOS – The League Management Company (LMC) has revealed the agreement it entered with the national broadcast station, Nigeria Television Authority. In an interview with select journalists on why the league has continually not been shown on TV, Dikko blamed the huge investment needed to upgrade NTA equipment and their dilapidated nature to the TV absence. He said that NTA and the LMC were still putting heads together to find investors to put the equipment to good uses, saying the deal would still see league matches on the national content soon. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “The agreement with NTA is first and foremost to use their vast equipment to set up the production capabilities needed to produce the NPFL matches. “But huge investment is needed to upgrade the equipment to current best standards and we have worked closely with NTA in this regards but things were delayed for obvious reasons with all this distraction.